The [v2 docs show an example](http://vee-validate.logaretm.com/v2/guide/flags.html#introduction) that iterates `this.fields`  (instead of `this.$validator.fields`) via [`Object.keys`](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Object/keys):

```js
// MyComponent.vue
export default {
  // ...
  computed: {
    isFormDirty() {
      return Object.keys(this.fields).some(key =&gt; this.fields[key].dirty);
    }
  },
  //...
}
```

Using that example, your computed prop would be:

```js
// MyComponent.vue
export default {
  // ...
  computed: {
    isFormTouchedOrInvalid() {
      return Object.keys(this.fields).some(key =&gt; this.fields[key].touched || this.fields[key].invalid);
    }
  },
  //...
}
